cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CL

The paper deals with land use and land cover classification using Earth observation sensors, which involves image processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of sequential encoder-decoder structures, which are commonly used in natural language processing and speech recognition, indicating a possible connection to cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of machine learning models for classification suggests a connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
